            "hed_transform": "upper",
            "dek": "Leica’s smallest gesture toward perfection.",
            "dek_bold": false,
            "dek_italic": false,
            "dek_align": "center",
            "body": "<p>The <em>Leica Mini</em> was never meant to impress only to notice. Small, black, and unassuming, it slips into a pocket and asks for nothing in return but attention. Its single fixed lens turns restraint into poetry, rewarding patience more than precision. Where other cameras perform, the Mini simply observes. It’s the kind of object that disappears in your hand until the shutter clicks and suddenly, what felt ordinary becomes tender, framed, remembered.</p>",
